I. The Rights of The Common Citizens

- A common citizen is a regular person living within the Empire that is not royalty or military personnel, that was born within Imperial lands, or signed up with the offices of Imperial Citizenship.

- Common citizens of the Empire are all considered equal and do not have any perks based on race, religion, or any other cultural factor.

- Common citizens have the right to appeal to the Elder Council to present a petition.

- Common citizens have the right to own property as long as the Imperial Chamber of Commerce is notified and taxes are paid.

- Common citizens have the right to carry a weapon as long as it is sheathed at all times unless there is an emergency.

- The Common Citizen is first obliged to serve the Emperor, then the Empire, then the Jarl, Councilor, or Count, and then the Divines.
